<kml>

<concept name=Be-Restrained>
<superconcept name=Be-Obstructed>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Be-Restrained>
  <definition>object unable to Move</definition>
  <requiredslot name=object>
    <restriction>may not be the <slot>object</slot> of any
      <conceptref name=Move> Event
    </restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <wnsynsets><adj>restrained#2
  </adj></wnsynsets>
  <wnsynsets>--
  </wnsynsets>
</component>

<musing>
The semantics of Be-Restrained are captured as conditions of the Actions
that put an <slot>object</slot> into this state (<conceptref name=Restrain>),
that take an <slot>object</slot> out of this state 
(<conceptref name=Unrestrain>) and that are prevented by this state 
(<conceptref name=Move>).
</musing>

</kml>


